(406, 1, '2017-12-18 06:55:22', '2017-12-18 06:55:22', 'The holidays are a time to spend with friends and family celebrating. Holiday traditions including meals, gifts, family activities, and parties all require work. Someone has to take care of all the details to make those times memorable.\r\n\r\nMore than likely, it is you. But, who takes care of you during <a href=\"http://womanitely.com/ways-waste-christmas-day/\">the hustle and bustle of Christmas</a>? You? You need to take care of yourself during these busy times as well. Try some of these ideas as you work to make everyone else’s holidays wonderful.\r\n<h2>1. Rest</h2>\r\nOf course, you probably knew this would be on the list, and it might be easier said than done when you have tons of things to do during the holidays. But, it is very important to have the proper rest to take good care of yourself.\r\n\r\nSome people struggle with getting good rest especially when they are stressed. Try some of these simple ways to help you get the rest you need to be good to yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Take naps. If you can get a nap in for a few minutes, do it. If your body feels the need to have more sleep, indulge yourself with a longer nap.</li>\r\n 	<li>Take it easy on the caffeine and other stimulants. Drink hot decaffeinated tea before bedtime to calm and soothe your body.</li>\r\n 	<li>Do not rely on alcohol to help you sleep. You need quality sleep, not sleep to wear off an alcohol buzz.</li>\r\n 	<li>Be sure to get to bed at a good time so you <a href=\"http://womanitely.com/things-eliminate-bedroom-better-sleep/\">get the amount of sleep you need</a> to wake up ready to take on the world.</li>\r\n</ul>', '3 Secrets to Staying Relaxed During the Holidays', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '3-secrets-to-staying-relaxed-during-the-holidays', '', '', '2017-12-18 07:39:24', '2017-12-18 07:39:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/projects/webapp-vtj/?p=406', 0, 'post', '', 0),
